 A CATHOLIC priest, Rev. Father, Cyprian Kooro, has reportedly slumped and died while conducting mass in Port Harcourt, the Rivers State capital. A source said the morning mass was underway on Sunday at St. Helen Catholic Church, Ogbogoro when the priest suddenly collapsed. He said other officials of the church immediately surrounded the priest and rushed him to the University of Port Harcourt Teaching Hospital (UPTH). Another source from UPTH said he saw them bringing the priest to the hospital, adding that he was later pronounced dead. The health challenges of the priest that caused his collapse could not be confirmed. The source said, â€œA catholic priest has reportedly slumped and died celebrating mass in Port Harcourt. The priest slumped after the homily. 